chr3	136403035	148341113	3q24 Region (includes ZIC1)	loss	3q24 Region (includes ZIC1) is associated with Deletions or duplications involving 3q24 with ZIC1 are linked to Dandy–Walker malformation, cerebellar hypoplasia, and variable developmental delay. Key genes: ZIC1; ZIC4. Care usually involves developmental and educational support, regular health checks for organ involvement, and management of seizures or growth concerns where relevant. The presentation and severity can vary widely, even among individuals with the same deletion. (OMIM: 614019)
chr3	195756054	197344662	3q29 recurrent region (includes DLG1)	loss	3q29 Microdeletion is associated with Recurrent 1.6 Mb 3q29 deletion confers risk for developmental delay, microcephaly, feeding problems, neuropsychiatric disorders (ASD/ADHD/schizophrenia), and variable congenital anomalies. Key genes: PAK2; DLG1; FBXO45. Care usually involves developmental and educational support, regular health checks for organ involvement, and management of seizures or growth concerns where relevant. The presentation and severity can vary widely, even among individuals with the same deletion. (OMIM: 609425)
